<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:normal'><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:
13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>Myocarditis is a heart
disease in which inflammation affects the heart muscle itself - the
myocardium.&nbsp;The disease is multifaceted, it can proceed latently and
imperceptibly, sometimes cause severe heart failure.&nbsp;There are many
reasons for myocarditis: viruses, bacteria, fungi, parasites;&nbsp;toxins and
poisons, medications, or a person's own immune system can cause
inflammation.&nbsp;The disease can proceed both acutely, with a rapid worsening
of symptoms, and for a long time, up to several months.</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:normal'><b><span lang=EN-US
style='font-size:18.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>The
disease is also known as</span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:
14.0pt;margin-left:0in;line-height:normal'><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:
13.5pt;font-family:"Times New Roman",serif;color:black'>Myocarditis differs in
the types of infection that cause it:</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-top:14.0pt;margin-left:64.9pt;text-indent:
-.25in;line-height:normal'><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Symbol;
